Project Title:
Login and Registration Web Application using Servlets and JSP

✅ Objective:
To develop a secure and user-friendly web application that allows users to register, log in, and manage sessions, using Java Servlets, JSP, and JDBC with MySQL as the backend database.

✅ Key Features:
User Registration:

Form to capture username, email, and password.

Validates unique usernames and stores encrypted passwords.

User Login:

Authenticates user credentials against the database.

On success, redirects to a welcome/dashboard page.

Session Management:

Tracks logged-in users using HttpSession.

Prevents unauthorized access to protected pages.

Logout Functionality:

Destroys the session and redirects to the login page.

Input Validation:

Basic form validation using JSP and JavaScript (if added).

Database Integration:

Uses JDBC to connect with MySQL.

Tables: users(id, username, email, password)

✅ Technology Stack:
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JSP

Backend: Java Servlets, JDBC

Database: MySQL

Tools/Server: Apache Tomcat